The paper is about open-domain question answering, which involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques. The paper proposes a new probabilistic formulation and a Hierarchical Answer Spans Model (HAS-QA) to tackle the challenges in this task. Based on this information, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. Other likely sub-categories include cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), which are all relevant to the topic of the paper.
